AN ACT making appropriations to the Nevada System of Higher Education for
expenditures related to instruction that are due to caseload adjustments
at certain institutions within the System; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. There is hereby appropriated from the State General Fund to the
2 Nevada System of Higher Education the sum of $4,325,366 for expenditures related
3 to instruction that are due to caseload adjustments at the University of Nevada, Las
4 Vegas.
5 Sec. 2. There is hereby appropriated from the State General Fund to the
6 Nevada System of Higher Education the sum of [$303,836] $291,526 for
7 expenditures related to instruction that are due to caseload adjustments at Nevada
8 State University.
9 Sec. 3. There is hereby appropriated from the State General Fund to the
10 Nevada System of Higher Education the sum of $1,963,392 for expenditures related
11 to instruction that are due to caseload adjustments at the College of Southern
12 Nevada.
13 Sec. 4. There is hereby appropriated from the State General Fund to the
14 Nevada System of Higher Education the sum of $938,124 for expenditures related
15 to instruction that are due to caseload adjustments at Western Nevada College.
16 Sec. 5. There is hereby appropriated from the State General Fund to the
17 Nevada System of Higher Education the sum of $2,203,368 for expenditures related

